Source: dnfs
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Darren Starr <darren@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 10), dh-dkms, dh-sequence-dkms
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/darrenstarr/dnfs

Package: dnfs-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: dkms (>= 2.8.0), ${misc:Depends}
Description: DKMS source for NFS multipath client module
 Builds and installs a modified nfs.ko kernel module with:
  * NFS_MAX_CONNECTIONS bumped to 32 (up to 9 data TCP connections per mount)
  * Per-mount multipath client creation for remoteaddrs= support
  * Increased NFSv4.1 session slot concurrency
 .
 This DKMS package targets Ubuntu 26.04 (kernel 7.0.0-15-generic) and
 the Huawei OceanStor Pacific 9550 storage array. It is part of the
 Distributed NFS (dnfs) project.

Package: dnfs-tools
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, python3, fio, nfs-common, iproute2
Recommends: ansible
Description: NFS multipath tools and benchmarks
 Tools for configuring and benchmarking NFS multipath against
 Huawei OceanStor storage arrays:
  * dnfs-stress — 20+ minute NFS stress/performance test
  * Ansible playbooks for diskpool03 deployment (network, kernel, mounts,
    benchmark)
  * Full documentation and kernel patch series
